    "body": "If I read the [R data rangling cheatsheet](http://www.rstudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/data-wrangling-cheatsheet.pdf) right, then in R-land `df %>% group_by(...) %>% mutate(...)` (or `... %>% summarise(â€¦)`is basically `df.groupby(...).apply(...)` (i.e. apply the function to each group). Not sure if then `pipe` should map to different semantic (e.g. pipe in the complete gb object).\n"
